parameters: Umi "Kru... I heard you haven't been eating at all..."
Umi "If you don't eat... your body will..."
Kru "...After what happened... being betrayed like that..."
Ah... that's not what I want to say...
Kru "Being betrayed like that... how can I even eat?!"
Kru "Umi! ...You might be fine with it but..."
Umi "That's not true! ...That's not it at all..."

When I looked at the chieftain, he was on the floor with his hands down,
prostrating himself.
Chieftain: "No... I can't apologize enough to you two."

Chieftain: "This situation... it's my fault. I spoiled that Banka, let him
grow up without restraint... and if only I had more power..."
Kru: "Please wait... I... don't quite understand the situation."
Then I was told the whole story...

About how Chancellor Shif had been in hiding for a year, took over the
village with hypnotic magic, how Umi was taken as a hostage and made into a
concubine, how they were subjecting Umi to all sorts of sexual training to
resurrect Kusechirei, and probably involving Kru as part of that process.
Chieftain: "It was all to protect our people... I'm truly sorry..."

Chieftain: "I'm not asking for forgiveness... but Umi is still suffering!
Please... forgive Umi for what she's been through..."
Chieftain: "Ah... yes, of course! Please eat!"
Kru: "The one at fault is Shif. Not the villagers, not Umi."

Kru: "Now... we shouldn't be here when the guards come back. Please go
back."
Chieftain: "Ah... right. Then I shall take my leave..."

The story I was told today... Even after hearing it, it seems I can't look
at Umi the same way as before.

My feelings are still a mess, and it seems it will take some time to mend
them.
I took a bite of the cold porridge... Yes, this taste is...

The same taste I had when I fell off the cliff and was being nursed back to
health... It hasn't changed since then...

That's right. What has changed... Umi is still Umi. She hasn't become
someone else or anything like that...

What changed was me... I became suspicious and hurt, didn't try to confirm
the facts, and closed myself off in my own shell.

I forgot about love and promises, just to protect myself... not to protect
someone else...
I cried quietly as I took another spoonful of porridge, and then another.

As I chewed on what had changed, what hadn't, what was important, and what
I wanted to protect, tears fell...

They passed through my tongue, down my throat, through my chest, and
settled in my stomach. The porridge was completely cold, but before I knew
it, my body had warmed up.
Kru "Ah... yesterday's porridge... thank you for the meal..."
Umi "Kru... I see, you ate it... I'm glad... I'm glad..."
Kru "I'm sorry... I'm so sorry, Umi. For making you suffer..."
Umi "No... it's not like that... It's my fault... It's all my fault..."
Umi "I hurt Kru... I betrayed Kru..."
Kru "I'm not hurt... I haven't been betrayed..."
Chancellor Shif "Really now... what are you doing with my woman..."
Chancellor Shif "Plans have changed... you've caused me enough trouble..."
Kru "What are you planning to do!"

Chancellor Shif "We're going to perform the ceremony. Umi, head to the
altar room."

Chancellor Shif "Don't worry, you'll be joining her... Hey, you guys! Bring
Kru along!"
Kru "Tch! Let go! Let me go!"
I... what should I say, I wonder...

Kru: "Ah... yesterday's porridge... thank you for the meal..."
Umi: "Kru... I see, you ate it... I'm glad... I'm glad..."
Kru: "I'm sorry... I'm so sorry, Umi. For making you suffer..."
Umi: "It's not like that... it's not your fault... it's my fault..."
Umi: "I hurt Kru... I betrayed Kru..."
Kru: "I'm not hurt... I haven't been betrayed..."

Kru: "Umi... I've heard the story from the chief. I'm sorry, for not
realizing anything until now..."

Kru: "You were fighting alone... You were suffering alone... and I couldn't
do anything for you..."

Kru: "And yet... I felt as if I was the only one who got hurt, and I ended
up hurting you..."

Kru: "But after hearing the chief's story and eating your porridge, I
remembered various things. The time when I first met you, when I was
bedridden, the journeys we took together..."

Kru: "That you've always been supporting me, that it wasn't something to be
taken for granted, but something irreplaceable..."
Umi: "Sorry, sorry... Kru... you thought all that after eating porridge?"

Umi: "I see... No... it's just porridge, nothing special... but you're so
grateful for it... that's what I thought..."

Umi: "Hehehe... then, I'll make porridge again and owe Kru a favor. Each
time, you'll have to cherish me more and more..."
Then we spent time reminiscing and cracking a few jokes...
I could feel the tension deep inside my body gradually easing.

At the same time, I felt like the twisted thread of our relationship was
being mended.

The stiff knots were being untied by Kru's words, his expressions, his
scent...
The thread was wrinkled, frayed, and torn in places,
but I felt like we could tie it together again.
I firmly made that resolution in my heart.
So that we won't be apart again...
Umi: "Well then, I guess it's time to go."

Villager: "That's... the chieftain went to retrieve the spell of
destruction from the ruins deep within the Summoning Cave... and Shif found
out about it..."

Villager: "And now there's a skirmish between the villagers and the
kingdom's soldiers..."

Villager: "But... the chieftain and his party haven't returned at all...
maybe in the cave... they're already..."
Iburu: "Umi, go and save the chieftain!"

Iburu: "We'll hold off the kingdom's soldiers, but sooner or later they'll
overpower us... however, if we have the spell the chieftain spoke of,
perhaps..."
Iburu: "...Are you sure? These villagers betrayed you."
Kru: "I know they were being controlled. Besides..."
Kru: "I am the next chieftain of this village. I will protect it."
Iburu: "...I see... I leave the chieftain's matter in your hands."
Kru: "Umi... Let's hurry! I'm worried about the chieftains!"
